---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../../config/site';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn how the Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame preserves, celebrates, and inspires Colorado high school baseball umpiring."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
  pageType="AboutPage"
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'About', path: '/about/' }]}
>
  <div class="page-shell">
    <article class="page-surface about-story">
      <h1>About the Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame</h1>
      <p class="about-intro">The <strong>{site.name}</strong> is a living nonprofit program dedicated to preserving the history, celebrating the achievements, and inspiring future generations of Colorado high school baseball umpires.</p>
      <p>JRHOF.org is the permanent digital home for Hall of Fame history, community, events, and the people who help carry this legacy forward, including inductees, volunteers, sponsors, donors, and historical contributors.</p>

    <h2>Mission Statement</h2>
    <p>{site.mission}</p>

    <div class="about-columns">
      <figure>
        <img src="/images/joe_rossi_first_pitch.jpeg" alt="Joe Rossi at Coors Field with Dinger and a young baseball fan" width="3024" height="4032" />
      </figure>

      <div class="about-column-copy">
        <h2>Named in Joe Rossi’s Honor</h2>
        <p><strong>Joe Rossi</strong> is recognized in the existing Hall of Fame record as a leader, mentor, and important figure in Colorado high school baseball umpiring. This photo captures him throwing the ceremonial first pitch at a Rockies game.</p>
        <p>The Hall of Fame is named in Joe Rossi’s honor because his character, service, leadership, and dedication embody the values recognized by the Hall of Fame. The mission, however, is broader than one person: it exists to preserve and celebrate the wider legacy of Colorado high school baseball umpires.</p>

        <h2>Inductees</h2>
        <p>Inductees are recognized for outstanding contributions to high school baseball umpiring and the broader baseball community. Each profile helps preserve a story of service, leadership, mentorship, or achievement that should remain visible for future generations.</p>

        <h2>Impact &amp; Community</h2>
        <p>The Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame is more than an archive of names. It is a community-supported effort to keep Colorado’s baseball umpiring history alive through recognition, education, historical preservation, and future opportunities approved by the nonprofit’s board.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Looking Ahead</h2>
    <p>Looking to the future, the organization intends to keep expanding the public archive, strengthening annual traditions, and exploring ways to encourage future umpires without overstating programs before they are approved and funded.</p>

    <h2>Help Preserve the Record</h2>
    <p>The umpiring community is invited to help preserve stories, photographs, memories, banquet programs, tournament materials, and other historical records. Community contributions can help the Hall of Fame build a more complete and accurate account of Colorado high school baseball umpiring.</p>

    <h2>Get Involved</h2>
    <p>We invite you to be part of the Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame mission. Your support can help preserve these stories, honor Colorado’s baseball umpiring legacy, and keep this history accessible to the people who care about it.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-story h1 { margin-bottom: 1.35rem; text-align: center; font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.5vw, 2.75rem); }
  .about-story h2 { margin: 1.7rem 0 .65rem; font-size: clamp(1.65rem, 2.5vw, 2rem); }
  .about-intro { margin-bottom: 1.3rem; }
  .about-columns { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, .9fr) minmax(0, 1fr); gap: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.75rem); align-items: start; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .about-columns figure { margin: 0; }
  .about-columns img { display: block; width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 3 / 4; object-fit: cover; object-position: center; border-radius: 10px; }
  .about-column-copy h2:first-child { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .about-column-copy p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .about-story h1 { font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 9vw, 2.4rem); }
    .about-story h2 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
    .about-columns { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: .4rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
    .about-columns figure { width: min(100%, 340px); margin-inline: auto; }
    .about-column-copy h2:first-child { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  }
</style>
